{"TopicId":215953,"ForumId":119,"TopicTitle":"Runway Length","CreatedByName":"tg626","CreatedById":112361,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-26T21:34:04Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"tg626","CreatedById":112361,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-26T21:34:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow long are the parallel runways in KSP2?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn 1 it was 2.5km long, but all these \u0022land speed\u0022 videos make it look WAY longer in KSP2.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tg626","CreatedById":112361,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-05T23:44:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNobody? \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:(\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_sad.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:(\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Little 908","CreatedById":228185,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-06T00:57:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224269395\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215953\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221680738260\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022112361\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022tg626\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, tg626 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNobody? \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:(\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_sad.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:(\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ndon\u0027t think anybody knows, but the ksp 1 runway is 2.5km so maybe it\u0027s the same length?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bej Kerman","CreatedById":182413,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-06T01:00:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224269408\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215953\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221680742662\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022228185\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Little 908\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, Little 908 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ndon\u0027t think anybody knows, but the ksp 1 runway is 2.5km so maybe it\u0027s the same length?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt isn\u0027t.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-06T01:59:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf I had the game, I\u0027d happily put something on one end, drive to the other end, and tell you the distance.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut I can\u0027t \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E Maybe after the science update drops I\u0027ll buy the game and if no one has answered your question, I\u0027ll do it then.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Little 908","CreatedById":228185,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-06T04:36:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224269418\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215953\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221680746360\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002273725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Superfluous J\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Superfluous J said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf I had the game, I\u0027d happily put something on one end, drive to the other end, and tell you the distance.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut I can\u0027t \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E Maybe after the science update drops I\u0027ll buy the game and if no one has answered your question, I\u0027ll do it then.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIm actually confused if you have either game or not, you\u2019re way too convincing lol\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"razark","CreatedById":32993,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-06T05:31:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t know the exact measurements, except Runway 36/18 is \u003Cstrong\u003Every\u003C/strong\u003E short, but wide as hell!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Periple","CreatedById":225622,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-06T05:37:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey\u2019re a bit over 7 kilometers. That\u2019s a lot of runway! I did Klapaucius\u2019s drag race challenge, that\u2019s how I know.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022?imw=5000\u0026amp;imh=5000\u0026amp;ima=fit\u0026amp;impolicy=Lett\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022166.67\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://steamuserimages-a.akamaihd.net/ugc/2013710564202173109/D43B321D1113E107ACBD4A68B4CB80D08195D8D8/?imw=5000\u0026amp;imh=5000\u0026amp;ima=fit\u0026amp;impolicy=Letterbox\u0026amp;imcolor=%23000000\u0026amp;letterbox=false\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-06T06:04:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNow on to question 2: Are they flat like KSP1\u0027s runways, or do they curve to match the surface of the planet like any reasonable runway would do?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JoeSchmuckatelli","CreatedById":154477,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-06T06:07:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224269454\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215953\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221680761081\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002273725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Superfluous J\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, Superfluous J said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNow on to question 2: Are they flat like KSP1\u0027s runways, or do they curve to match the surface of the planet like any reasonable runway would do?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think they are flat - based off of trying to fly a plane that did not want to, and having to go to where the ground fell away to get off it.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCourse that\u0027s a couple of weeks ago and things may have changed\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DerkyJerkyWreaksHavoc","CreatedById":207646,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-06T11:38:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224265931\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215953\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221679866444\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022112361\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022tg626\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 3/26/2023 at 5:34 PM, tg626 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow long are the parallel runways in KSP2?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn 1 it was 2.5km long, but all these \u0022land speed\u0022 videos make it look WAY longer in KSP2.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRunway looks to be at least 7km long (~4.375 miles for us americans or about 23,100ft long, which is about 12,000 feet longer than most international airport runways)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI will say we can simply measure it by driving a vehicle to one end of the runway and have the other one at the opposite end and then make the vehicles target each other for a more accurate measure\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224269451\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215953\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221680759454\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022225622\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Periple\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, Periple said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey\u2019re a bit over 7 kilometers. That\u2019s a lot of runway! I did Klapaucius\u2019s drag race challenge, that\u2019s how I know.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://steamuserimages-a.akamaihd.net/ugc/2013710564202173109/D43B321D1113E107ACBD4A68B4CB80D08195D8D8/?imw=5000\u0026amp;imh=5000\u0026amp;ima=fit\u0026amp;impolicy=Letterbox\u0026amp;imcolor=%23000000\u0026amp;letterbox=false\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022?imw=5000\u0026amp;imh=5000\u0026amp;ima=fit\u0026amp;impolicy=Lett\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022166.67\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://steamuserimages-a.akamaihd.net/ugc/2013710564202173109/D43B321D1113E107ACBD4A68B4CB80D08195D8D8/?imw=5000\u0026amp;imh=5000\u0026amp;ima=fit\u0026amp;impolicy=Letterbox\u0026amp;imcolor=%23000000\u0026amp;letterbox=false\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nbtw \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/225622-periple/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022225622\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/225622-periple/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Periple\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0believe it or not but i actually made my prediction before i saw your screenshot, since i almost always scroll to the bottom.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Periple","CreatedById":225622,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-06T11:46:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI looked it up and they\u0027re about 2 km longer than the longest runway on Earth. Kerbals love a good runway!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DerkyJerkyWreaksHavoc","CreatedById":207646,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-06T11:49:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224269408\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215953\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221680742662\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022228185\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Little 908\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 hours ago, Little 908 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ndon\u0027t think anybody knows, but the ksp 1 runway is 2.5km so maybe it\u0027s the same length?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ndefinitely note\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224269514\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215953\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221680781589\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022225622\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Periple\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 minutes ago, Periple said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI looked it up and they\u0027re about 2 km longer than the longest runway on Earth. Kerbals love a good runway!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nare you looking at the chinese military runway or KEDW\u0027s asphalt runways or KEDW\u0027s Sandbed runways (which are EXTREMELY LONG)?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI know one day, we\u0027re going to whine, bicker, and moan that the runways aren\u0027t long enough... just like we did in the last game lol (maybe jk)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-04-06T11:51:46Z\u0022 title=\u002204/06/2023 11:51  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EApril 6, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by DAFATRONALDO2007 IN SPACE\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Periple","CreatedById":225622,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-06T11:51:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224269516\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215953\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221680781763\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022207646\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DAFATRONALDO2007 IN SPACE\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, DAFATRONALDO2007 IN SPACE said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nare you looking at the chinese military runway or KEDW\u0027s asphalt runways or KEDW\u0027s Sandbed runways (which are EXTREMELY LONG)?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI just looked them up from here!\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_longest_runways\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_longest_runways\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DerkyJerkyWreaksHavoc","CreatedById":207646,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-06T11:54:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224269518\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215953\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221680781902\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022225622\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Periple\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Periple said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI just looked them up from here!\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_longest_runways\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_longest_runways\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, that\u0027s longest paved runway... I know KEDW\u0027s largest runway\u0027s look like this:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022OIP.enXt7cKj-7damBV-VOs7SQHaE3?pid=ImgDe\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002265.61\u0022 height=\u0022311\u0022 width=\u0022474\u0022 src=\u0022https://tse4.mm.bing.net/th/id/OIP.enXt7cKj-7damBV-VOs7SQHaE3?pid=ImgDet\u0026amp;rs=1\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThese runways reach over 20,000 feet long easily and they technically can go much farther since its all flat. they just choose not to\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/225622-periple/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022225622\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/225622-periple/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Periple\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Edwards_Air_Force_Base#Infrastructure_and_facilities\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EEdwards Air Force Base - Wikipedia\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRead the length of runway 17/35.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNow truly, us americans... We have gone kerbal\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"whatsEJstandfor","CreatedById":220814,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-06T16:56:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224269454\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215953\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221680761081\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002273725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Superfluous J\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 hours ago, Superfluous J said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNow on to question 2: Are they flat like KSP1\u0027s runways, or do they curve to match the surface of the planet like any reasonable runway would do?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBased on my testing from pre-patch-one, they\u0027re flat, not conforming to the curvature of the planet. This causes a vehicle to roll from either end towards a point near the east end (I didn\u0027t realize this was what I was testing until \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/226149-sea_kerman/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022226149\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/226149-sea_kerman/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Sea_Kerman\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0pointed it out)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022220814\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed1368218955\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/213481-the-ksc-runways-are-not-perfectly-level/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0026amp;comment=4245174\u0026amp;embedComment=4245174\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment#comment-4245174\u0022 style=\u0022height:264px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-04-06T16:58:24Z\u0022 title=\u002204/06/2023 04:58  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EApril 6, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by whatsEJstandfor\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tg626","CreatedById":112361,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-06T22:11:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224269611\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215953\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221680800213\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022220814\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022whatsEJstandfor\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, whatsEJstandfor said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis causes a vehicle to roll from either end towards a point near the east end\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThen they ARE flat, but the axis is near the east end.\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nThanks for the confirmations about the length everyone. WOW....\u00A0 I can only assume with Kerbin still being 600000km that the whole of the land at \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E is now level or nearly, otherwise you\u0027d absolutely notice one end or both being SUPER elevated above the average terrain beside it. Probably the best solution to that problem really.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-07T02:42:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m no programmer but it feels like they could just slap a \u0022runway\u0022 texture on the planet surface, instead of putting all of \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E on a big block.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Lyneira","CreatedById":149515,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-11T09:02:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224269761\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215953\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221680835322\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002273725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Superfluous J\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 4/7/2023 at 4:42 AM, Superfluous J said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m no programmer but it feels like they could just slap a \u0022runway\u0022 texture on the planet surface, instead of putting all of \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E on a big block.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPerhaps a part of the reason they haven\u0027t is because driving over flat PQS terrain at high speed tends to result in the landing gear doing a \u0022hiccup\u0022 now and then. (probably when crossing some mesh boundaries) It tends to send my high speed rover attempts into a spin...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-12T03:04:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224271213\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215953\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221681203747\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022149515\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Lyneira\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n18 hours ago, Lyneira said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPerhaps a part of the reason they haven\u0027t is because driving over flat PQS terrain at high speed tends to result in the landing gear doing a \u0022hiccup\u0022 now and then. (probably when crossing some mesh boundaries) It tends to send my high speed rover attempts into a spin...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve seen that on hills and whatnot (in KSP1) but like on Minmus\u0027 flats that are sections of a PERFECT sphere, I\u0027ve never had that problem.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Lyneira","CreatedById":149515,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-12T09:00:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224271486\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215953\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221681268661\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002273725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Superfluous J\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, Superfluous J said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve seen that on hills and whatnot (in KSP1) but like on Minmus\u0027 flats that are sections of a PERFECT sphere, I\u0027ve never had that problem.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI took said rover to the Minmus flats a couple days ago and I did have the problem there as well. Picture of it, here on Ike.\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Ike-racing-rover.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022120.00\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1074737019944706048/1094723695114723409/Ike-racing-rover.jpg\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt may be those landing gear at the back specifically though, they sometimes have a tendency to sink into terrain and pop out as well, knocking the rover into the air.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}